<h1>Hello from Rails!</h1>
<p>It is now <%= @time %></p>
<p>
  Time to say
  <%= link_to "Goodbye", say_goodbye_path %>!
</p>

<p>Addition: what is 1 + 2? Answer: <%= 1 + 2 %></p>
<p>Concatenation: adding cow + boy equals: <%= "cow" + "boy" %></p>
<p>The time in one our: <%= 1.hour.from_now.localtime %></p>

<p>A call to the following Ruby method returns a list of all the files in the current directory <b><em>@files = dir.glob('*')</em></b></p>
<p> Here's an output for files in @files:</p>
<ul>
  <% @files.each do |file| %>
  <li>file name is <%= file %></li>
  <% end %>
</ul>
